5:["$","p","7",{"className":"article-p","children":["Only 11% were using any form of scan-based attribution — and this includes basic QR codes for menus, which don't actually track attribution."]}]
6:["$","h2","8",{"className":"article-h2","children":"The Spending Paradox"}]
7:["$","p","9",{"className":"article-p","children":["The same restaurants spending an average of $820/month on marketing couldn't tell us what was working. The data reveals a paradox: the businesses with the least attribution capability are spending the most on unattributable channels."]}]
8:["$","p","10",{"className":"article-p","children":["Specifically:"]}]
9:["$","ul","11",{"className":"article-list","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Instagram/Meta ads:"}]," Average spend $340/month. Attribution rate: 3% (self-reported as \"confident\" attribution)"]}],["$","li","1",{"children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Influencer posts:"}]," Average spend $280/month. Attribution rate: 1%"]}],["$","li","2",{"children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Google Ads:"}]," Average spend $200/month. Attribution rate: 12% (Google's own conversion tracking, website visits only)"]}]]}]
a:["$","p","12",{"className":"article-p","children":["The conclusion is uncomfortable: NYC restaurants are spending $820/month on average and are confident in the attribution of approximately ",["$","strong","1",{"children":"$$50"}]," of it."]}]
b:["$","h2","13",{"className":"article-h2","children":"What Owners Said They Wanted"}]
