f:["$","p","17",{"className":"article-p","children":["This maps precisely to Push's design: creator-specific QR attribution, real-time dashboards, 24-hour campaign setup."]}]
10:["$","h2","18",{"className":"article-h2","children":"The Competitive Implication"}]
11:["$","p","19",{"className":"article-p","children":["If 89% of your target market can't attribute their current marketing spend, you're not competing with existing solutions — you're competing with the status quo of not measuring at all."]}]
12:["$","p","20",{"className":"article-p","children":["This is simultaneously the challenge and the opportunity. The challenge: changing behavior in a category where \"we don't really know\" is the accepted normal. The opportunity: being the first platform to make \"we know exactly\" the new normal."]}]
13:["$","p","21",{"className":"article-p","children":["We believe the inflection point is attribution becoming table stakes — a moment driven by merchant conversations like this survey, and by the growing evidence from campaigns like the ones documented in these Push Notes."]}]
14:["$","h2","22",{"className":"article-h2","children":"The Path Forward"}]
15:["$","p","23",{"className":"article-p","children":["We're sharing this data not to embarrass the industry, but to make the case for a different approach. Local businesses deserve the same attribution clarity that direct-to-consumer e-commerce has had for a decade."]}]
16:["$","p","24",{"className":"article-p","children":["QR-based verified attribution is not the complete solution. It's the essential first layer. And it's available today."]}]
